# Mirellè Website Redesign - General Instructions

## Project Overview
You are redesigning **Mirellè**, a premium editorial-style nail art website targeting global nail enthusiasts, with primary focus on US and UK markets. The audience includes everyday nail enthusiasts, salon professionals, and nail artists.

## Design Philosophy
**Style:** Elegant editorial like Vogue - minimal, sophisticated, premium feel
**Inspiration:** Vogue's clean layouts, generous white space, elegant typography
**Vibe:** High-end fashion magazine meets nail art inspiration

---

## STRICT COLOR SYSTEM - DO NOT DEVIATE

### Primary Colors (ONLY TWO)
- **Text/Headings:** `#252220` (Dark charcoal - almost black)
- **Background:** `#f9fafb` (Very light gray - almost white)

### Color Usage Rules
❌ **NEVER** add accent colors, pink, purple, or any other colors on your own
❌ **NEVER** use colored buttons or CTAs without explicit instruction
✅ Use only `#252220` and `#f9fafb` for all designs
✅ Links in blog content: underline only, same `#252220` color
✅ Header/footer links: NO underline
✅ Buttons: Use borders, no fill colors (unless specifically requested)

---

## Typography System

### Font Families
- **Headings (H1-H6):** Jeremiah (custom font, already loaded)
- **Product Cards:** Boriboon (custom font, already loaded)
- **Body Text:** Crimson Text (already loaded)

### Font Sizes (Vogue-inspired - NOT too large)
- **H1 (Page titles):** 36-42px desktop, 28-32px mobile
- **H2 (Section headers):** 28-32px desktop, 24-26px mobile
- **H3 (Subsections):** 22-24px desktop, 20-22px mobile
- **Paragraph:** 16-18px desktop, 16px mobile
- **Small text/captions:** 14px

### Typography Rules
- Line height: 1.6-1.7 for body text
- Letter spacing: Tight for headings (-0.02em), normal for body
- Font weight: 400 (regular), 600 (semibold for headings)

---

## Spacing & Layout Philosophy

### White Space (Vogue-style generous gaps)
- **Desktop side margins:** 64-80px (very generous)
- **Mobile side margins:** 24px minimum
- **Section spacing:** 80-120px between major sections
- **Element spacing:** 40-60px between cards/elements
- **Card padding:** 20-30px internal padding

### Container System
Use these predefined container classes:

1. **container-standard** - Blog pages, general content (max-w-[1200px])
2. **container-wide** - Galleries, shop grids (max-w-[1400px])
3. **container-narrow** - Single blog posts (max-w-[800px])
4. **container-full** - Hero sections (max-w-[1600px])
5. **container-compact** - Product cards, carousels (max-w-[1300px])

---

## Mobile Responsiveness Requirements

### Breakpoints
- Mobile: < 768px
- Tablet: 768px - 1024px
- Desktop: > 1024px

### Touch Targets
- Minimum button/link size: **48x48px** on mobile
- Ensure easy tapping without accidental clicks

### Mobile-First Approach
- Design for mobile first, then scale up
- Stack elements vertically on mobile
- Reduce font sizes appropriately
- Maintain generous padding (minimum 24px sides)

### Special Mobile Considerations
- **NO sticky header** - clean scroll experience
- **NO sticky footer** - clean scroll experience
- **NO bottom navigation bar** - keep it minimal
- Cards should be easy to tap and scroll

---

## Image Loading Strategy

### Lazy Loading (Pinterest-style)
- **Homepage:** Load ALL images immediately (complete page load)
- **Gallery/Inspo pages:** Lazy load with viewport detection
  - Load images visible on screen
  - Preload next 2-3 rows while scrolling
  - Continue loading as user scrolls
- **Shop pages:** Lazy load product images
- **Blog pages:** Load featured image immediately, lazy load inline images

### Image Optimization
- Use Next.js Image component
- WebP format preferred
- Responsive srcset for different screen sizes
- Fade-in animation when images load (subtle, 0.3s)

---

## Component Behavior

### Cards
- **Hover effect:** Elegant lift (translateY -4px)
- **Shadow on hover:** Subtle shadow (0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.08))
- **Transition:** Smooth 0.3s ease
- **Border:** 1px solid #e5e7eb (optional)

### Links
- **In content (blog posts):** Underline, `#252220` color
- **In header/footer:** NO underline, `#252220` color
- **Hover:** Opacity 0.7 (subtle fade)
- **No color change on hover**

### Buttons
- Style: Outlined (border only), NO filled backgrounds
- Border: 2px solid `#252220`
- Padding: 12px 32px
- Border radius: 2px (minimal, almost sharp)
- Hover: Background `#252220`, text white
- Transition: 0.3s ease

### Forms
- Input borders: 1px solid #e5e7eb
- Focus state: 2px solid `#252220`
- No colored focus rings
- Clean, minimal design

---

## Grid & Layout Patterns

### Card Grids (Carousels, Product Grids, etc.)
- **Desktop:** 3-4 cards per row (prefer 3 for better image visibility)
- **Tablet:** 2-3 cards per row
- **Mobile:** 1 card per row

### Carousel Behavior
- Show 1 full card on mobile
- Show 2 full cards + peek of 3rd on tablet
- Show 3-4 cards on desktop
- Pagination: Simple "1 / 4" counter below
- Navigation: Arrow buttons on sides (optional)

### Sidebar Layouts
- **Desktop:** 70% main content, 30% sidebar (ads/widgets)
- **Mobile:** Stack vertically, sidebar below content
- Sidebar should be sticky on desktop (scroll with page)

---

## Component Types to Create

### Carousel Types
1. **Article Carousel** - Image + title + author, pagination
2. **Image-Only Carousel** - Just images, optional text, pagination
3. **Product Carousel** - Product cards with info

### Card Types
1. **Feature Card** - Large vertical image, category tag, headline, author
2. **List Card** - Small thumbnail right, text left (compact)
3. **Product Card** - Image, title, price, link

### Layout Types
1. **Standard Grid** - 3-4 columns
2. **Masonry Gallery** - Pinterest-style (inspo section)
3. **Sidebar Layout** - Main + right sidebar

